I added the awards and distinctions section, as others have agreed to it on the talk page. I removed certain phrases that appeared to be promotional or non-neutral, and instead only kept statements that were referenced by other sources, and included no opinions. Please describe any concerns on the talk page.

I opened discussion on talk page of this article, please respond before deleting the edits. As I have explained earlier, this section is a necessary section for an article as notable as this. I am not trying to engage in an edit war, please explain why you are removing the content unnecessarily.

The description of the school's opportunities and courses is necessary, and the section for awards and rankings is also necessary. It is important to include all aspects of a subject in an encyclopedia, including the subjects awards and distinctions (if any). Other institution pages also have an awards and rankings section. It is also important to add descriptions and views on the subject from the media and news reporting, such as NYT (if any).

The article also sounds to be promoting the school rather than informing the reader about the school.

I think it is necessary to include many of the details of the school that Pmmp1234 included, but some changes needed to be made. The description of each academy's course offerings should be kept, because it gives information about the courses taken in each academy, just as how an institution would give certain courses to students with certain majors, and that's definitely encyclopedic. I also moved the rankings to a new section of the page called Awards, Rankings & Distinctions.
